Title: Consistent reduction of N=2 -> N=1 four dimensional supergravity coupled

to matterAuthors: L. Andrianopoli, R. D'Auria, S. Ferrara

Comments: LaTeX, 16 pages

Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B628 (2002) 387-403

We analyze the constraints which follow both on the geometry and on the gaugesector for a consistent supergravity reduction of a general matter-coupled N=2supergravity theory in four dimensions. These constraints can be derived in anelegant way by looking at the fermionic sector of the theory.